<br>
Met you only once in-game.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I see no problem with playing EQ to beat it, but I think the real problem is that there is no way to to truly beat EQ. There's just too many ways to be considered The Best (tm) at this particular programming of pixels and polygons. Everquest is just that, ever-questing. Constant questing for loot, money, or experience, depending on one's preference. If the game was static you could be the best, but it's not. New content is added every patch and expansion.<br>
<br>
Look at Starcraft for example. It's an online game but the game itself is unchanging. You can be quantified The Best there by being #1 on the Bnet ladder rankings. The mechanics for beating the game don't change. Blizzard isn't suddenly going to add four new fighters that allowing instant power recharging and run like a marine on stims along with cloak abilities every month. Blizzard's not going to suddenly reduce the cost of zerg ultralisks by half because they're slow. There are no new expansions coming out every year for Starcraft. <br>
<br>
There's really no way to be #1 here. No way to beat a game that's constantly changing. You don't know whether you'll be upgraded one patch or have the infamous VI nerf stick broken over your class the next.<br>
<br>
I think what you're looking for in EQ doesn't really exist, for the most part. All games I've seen with an online component are social in some way or another, through the development of clans, guilds, and the like. Humans are just social creatures like that. You can even say life can be considered a game. People log on to life to find love, friends, ph4t l3wt5 (like that hi-fi Dolby Digital 5.1 surround sound home theater <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), family, and money. Everquest is really just an extension of that in little binary digits. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><br><b>Anaxo</b>
